Salesforce has strong agreement language about the use of data here  - their stance has been We do not collect or store non-pseudonymized personal data on the Platform, nor do we allow our Customers to do so. Will go with Salesforce - or if remains, Hiep to submit through TMCR.

Per Michelle Frazier, this is related to eSupport pages and built/maintained by eSupport DEVs (Atif Malik - am349m).  The solution calls the Sprinklr API for the data that powers the widget experience on relevant e-Support article pages.  The data is part of the forums.att.com experience, also powered by Sprinklr.  That includes the user avatars (references as tags) in the attached screenshots.  Sprinklr does not maintain the content on the referenced pages.  Follow up with Atif re TMCR submittal.
